main event: An object was observed in Fitzgerald, Georgia on 16 April 1956, believed to possibly be the planet Venus.
interesting points: The object was initially reported to be silver-yellowish and round,The sighting lasted for 2 hours and 45 minutes,The object was visible both with the naked eye and through binoculars,Two aircraft were observed at high altitude during the sighting,Investigations concluded that the object was likely Venus based on its position and movement.
